parameters:
Male Informant: That attire...! What is someone from the
Magic Academy doing here!?

Mage Relm: We were asked by Dokusa-san to come here. If
possible, we would like to cooperate with you as informants.

Male Informant: He's so rough with people, I can't
understand a word he's saying. I can't work with someone
like that anymore!
Mage Relm: Ugh... I can't come up with a comeback...!

Priestess Sophia: Well, well, would you all mind letting us
speak with the representative here?

Lopos the Bull: I apologize, but as the representative here,
I must sever ties with Dokusa.
Priestess Sophia: Is there really no way at all?

Lopos the Bull: I'm sorry, but it's a decision that has been
made. Please go back.

Priestess Sophia: I see, I see... It's quite troublesome,
isn't it?

Priestess Sophia: Phew... I understand, let's resolve this
with violence.

Male Informant: What a woman! She's definitely acquainted
with Dokusa, she's a mess!
Mage Relm: Ugh... I can't deny it...!

Mage Relm: If it's come to this, I'll go all out! Now, even
if I have to force you, I'll make you nod your head!

Lopos the Bull: Hmph... Your strength is impressive, but we
won't waver from our decision.

Priestess Sophia: Could it be that you two... hehe, would
you like to have a private conversation in the back?

Priestess Sophia: Could you tell me the reason behind your
smile?

Lopos the Bull: Don't let anyone in, let the two of us have
a conversation.
Priestess Sophia: Oh my, you're quite strong...

Lopos the Bull: We are Tarasa war veterans, so we have work
to do. Please leave.

Ropos the Bull: You've come back, huh...! I'll make you try
again and again until you give up!

Ropos the Bull: Hmph... You may have some skill, but we
